On a month-on-month basis, price growth was at 1.0% in February, from 0.3% in the previous month. JOHANNESBURG - South Africaâ€™s headline consumer price inflation quickened to 4.6% year-on-year in February, from 4.5% in January, data from Statistics South Africa showed on Wednesday. On a month-on-month basis, price growth was at 1.0% in February, from 0.3% in the previous month. Core inflation, which excludes prices of food, non-alcoholic beverages, petrol and energy, rose to 3.8% year-on-year in February compared with a rate of 3.7% in January. On a month-on-month basis core inflation quickened to 1.2%, from 0.1% in the prior month.